      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The Northern Pacific is planning\nto change its present route of en-\ntrance into this city to l up through\nPeaceful valley. Thence through\nthe proposed Graves tunnel to the\nline east of town. This is the prob\nability that is worrying residents Of\nPeaceful valley. Real estate men\nhave bought extensively in that\npart of the city in the name of the\nNorthern Pacific Railway Co.\n\n\nA strip of 100 feet on the north\nside, or practically the whole of\nWilson St, has already been Sc\ncured.\n\n\nBY following water grade on\nHangman creek for little way af-\nter leaving Peaceful valley, a hill\nthat is almost unsurmountable with\nheavy tonnage may be evaded,\nthereby permitting heavier trains to\nbe pulled west from this city."
    }
